dct_title_s: Gelriae Cliviae Ivliae nec non Aliarum Regionum Adiacentium Nova Descriptio Michaelis Tramezini Formis ex Pontificis Max ac Veneti senatus in proximum decenmiun privilegio MDLV111
dct_description_sm: Bar scale on map given in "Millaria Gelria minora."
Map of Gelderland Province (of Holland), and adjacent areas, designed by the early Dutch cartographer Jacob van Derventor, and published by Michaelis Tramezini in Venice in 1558.
